Each day we are lucky enough to go to work at a place where we can explore new flavors, meet new people and be inspired by the state we live in.  Here at Lick Honest Ice Creams, we celebrate the farmers, produce, artisans and Texas nostalgia that surround us through the ice creams we create.  <!--more-->

&nbsp;

I’ve always been in love with both Texas and ice cream.  Growing up in Hallettsville, a small town settled by German and Czech immigrants, I had the great fortune of living in a community that appreciated and practiced the art of growing and crafting things in an honest way.   My grandparents had a farm and I relished walking in the fields and pastures with my family.  We’d walk in the shade and pick delicious, buttery Texas pecans, shelling and eating them as we took in the breeze.  I was always so impressed and proud to see my grandma selling her fresh produce at the farmers market on our town square.  This sense of pride I saw in my grandparents is what we all feel here toward our ice creams.

&nbsp;

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1666" alt="1-hallettsville" src="http://ilikelick.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/1-hallettsville.jpg" width="440" height="282" data-id="1666" />

&nbsp;

Every summer, which can extend from March to October, I made ice cream with my family.  We would of course make the standards but we also delighted in making flavors that featured the local bounty.  Pecan, peach and dewberry were my personal favorites.  We’d sit in the shade, one of us usually planted atop the ice cream maker, and one cranking away on the handle.   Now, we get to make ice cream like this (with the exception of the hand crank) everyday of the year.  From the local grass-fed milk and cream to the produce, chocolate and honey brought to us by the most amazing, down to earth farmers and artisans, we’re continually inspired.

&nbsp;

I share all of this as a way to convey just how connected I and all of us who work at Lick Honest Ice Creams feel to the ice creams we craft.  We get to make something we’re so proud of and head over heels in love with every day.  Thanks to all of our supporters for helping us do what we love to do.  We hope you love it too!

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: right;">- Anthony Sobotik, co-founder &amp; chef</p>
&nbsp;

