Our kitchen staff is awesome.  Although we’re forever growing – soon to open new shops and add our ice cream to the shelves of more grocery stores both big and small around the state – there are just a few skilled hands working every day to make our ice cream. <!--more--> They put the stickers on every pint, hand write the flavors on every pint lid, bake every cake and component from scratch, chop every bunch of herbs,  swirl every sauce into each tub of ice cream, and hand pack every pint.  They work really hard to make sure that the ice cream y’all enjoy is as good as it can possibly be.

&nbsp;

Emily leads the churning team.  She grew up in Austin, spent a few years in NYC, and (lucky for us) began working at Lick shortly after her return to Texas.  In Austin and in New York, Emily gained years of experience cooking great food for well respected restaurants, cafes, and catering companies.  She’s an exceptionally talented cook.  There’s a good chance that Emily inspired the delicious new flavor that we recently introduced and an even better chance that she churned it.  In all seriousness, Emily makes the most beautiful swirls we’ve ever seen.

&nbsp;

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1851" alt="9-hands" src="http://ilikelick.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/9-hands.jpg" width="440" height="282" data-id="1851" />

&nbsp;

Claire started at Lick writing lids and quickly took over all of our ice cream prep work.  After graduating from pastry school in Colorado, she moved to Austin to pursue chocolate.  She loves chocolate.  She makes the prettiest molded chocolates and sometimes brings them to work to share with the sweet fiends in the office.  (Thank you, Claire!)  We’re so lucky that Claire also loves ice cream because she’s really good at making it.  The beautifully executed cakes, luscious curds, sauces, and every one of our components are all thanks to her.

&nbsp;

Alyssa is a pastry school graduate, native Austinite, and newest addition to our team.  She came to us after a few months of high altitude baking in the mountains of Colorado.  She’s an avid baker and, unlike many, quickly mastered packing ice cream into a pint – it truly is so much harder than it looks!  She clearly knows how to wield a spatula.  And of all of us in the kitchen, Alyssa treats us to more homemade desserts than the rest of us combined.  (Did I mention that we like sweets?)

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: right;">- Diana Vassar, Kitchen Manager</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1858" alt="9-pints" src="http://ilikelick.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/9-pints.jpg" width="440" height="282" data-id="1858" /></p>

2014 was another exciting year in the kitchen!  It was the year of development &amp; growth.  It was the year of hard work.  It was trying at times but in the end I can honestly say it was a ton of fun.<!--more-->

&nbsp;

This year, we built our first walk-in freezer, began selling at Central Market and Whole Foods, opened our second store at Pearl in San Antonio, participated in so many awesome local events, made ice cream sandwiches, ice cream cakes, ice cream sundaes, ice cream milkshakes, and floats.  We introduced delicious new flavors and made, sold, and donated more ice cream than ever before!

&nbsp;

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1885" alt="10-minicones" src="http://ilikelick.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/10-minicones.jpg" width="440" height="282" data-id="1885" />

&nbsp;

We’re so thankful for our staff, everyone we work with, and all of our awesome customers.  Because of y’all, we can continue doing what we love.  Thank you for being a part of this incredible year.  I can't wait for everything that's in store for 2015.

&nbsp;

Happy New Year, everybody!

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: right;">- Diana Vassar, Kitchen Manager</p>
&nbsp;

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1886" alt="10-happynewyear" src="http://ilikelick.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/10-happynewyear.jpg" width="440" height="282" data-id="1886" />

Each day I get to come to work and share what I love with some truly amazing individuals.  We inspire each other, we laugh, we encourage one another, we work hard and we make some damn good ice cream.  To say that I am truly overwhelmed by their level of creativity, compassion and dedication is an understatement.<!--more-->

&nbsp;

So, it dawned on me that none of y'all get to have the pleasure of knowing these kind, genuine folks.  I just don't feel that is fair.  To remedy this, we're going to profile some of our staff over the next year.  I've compiled a list of questions for each person to complete that will allow you to get to know them as I do.

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: right;">-  Anthony Sobotik,  co-owner &amp; chef</p>
&nbsp;

First up is our lovely office manager.  Everyone,  meet Juliet!

&nbsp;

<strong>Full name: </strong>Juliet Anelie Dill

&nbsp;

<strong>Date of Birth</strong>:  December 8th, 1977

&nbsp;

<strong>Natural Hair Color</strong>:  Red!!

&nbsp;

<strong>Favorite color(s)</strong>:  Deep blue, Magenta, Purple, and Emerald Green

&nbsp;

<strong>What I love most about living in Austin</strong>:  Being a Mama of a 3.5 year old little boy, my husband and I love all the things Austin has to offer families.  There aren't many towns where you can go out and meet your friends, have a drink while the kids play, and listen to some amazing live music.  Austin also has so much art and community based events centered around nature, farming, and creativity.  In its heart though, Austin is a little hippie town with great style and a funky vibe that brings together an eclectic mix of people.  Last but certainly not least -- TacoDeli breakfast tacos.  When we moved to Boulder a few years ago, breakfast tacos were nowhere to be found and we were in a breakfast fog for the four year we lived there.

&nbsp;

<strong>Favorite musician (doesn't have to be Madonna, but it couldn't hurt)</strong>:  Well besides Madonna, of course... There's no way I can pick only one; my favorites are G. Love, John Butler, Art Tatum, Amos Lee, The Black Keys, Blind Melon, Van Morrisson, Eddie Bedder, Imogen Heap, and you know a lil' Beyonce never hurts.

&nbsp;

<strong>Cat or dog person: </strong>Dog!! (or hedgehog)

&nbsp;

<strong>Favorite 'life saying' or quote or 'words to live by': </strong>If you want to know what "should have" happened, look at what "did" happen.

&nbsp;

<strong>What I do at Lick</strong>:  I'm the office manager and right hand gal for the amazing owners, Anthony and Chad.  I handle wholesale, event coordination, bookkeeping, charitable donations, and anything else they throw my way.

&nbsp;

<strong>Why I love my job</strong>:  I love how Lick participates in the community and gives so much back to the people of Austin.  I love supporting local farms and artisans and on the flipside the magic that brings to our business.  I love how Lick truly is an honest company in every facet of the business.  I am grateful to work with an amazing group of individuals that light up my days.  Each and every member of our team has such a big heart and huge personality.  "The boys," as I collectively call Anthony and Chad, are two of the best bosses I could ask for.  They are incredibly approachable, always open to growth, and move through challenges with grace and humor.  It feels like we are all in this together and it's always a team effort.  But I will say that my most favorite thing about my job is how much I laugh.  Seriously.  My days are full of laughter and it makes my world a lighter place.

&nbsp;

<strong>Time with Lick</strong>:  9 months

&nbsp;

<strong>Why I love ice cream</strong>:  Ice cream makes everyone happy!

&nbsp;

<strong>Favorite flavor</strong>:  Blushing Blueberry.... Oh how I can't wait for its return.  A couple weeks ago, our kitchen manager, Diana, found some forgotten pints of it in the freezer and I thought I'd died and gone to heaven with a spoon.  Two scoops!

&nbsp;

