Did you know that there are 190 flavor combinations every day to choose from at our scoop shops?  That’s a new pairing every day for half a year!  Add that to the five flavors we rotate seasonally, six times per year, and you get 85 new flavor combinations every two months.  That’s tremendous.  And a ton of ice cream possibility.<!--more-->

&nbsp;

When we create a season’s flavor lineup, we want to create a story.  20 flavors narrate the story of the season, the holidays, Texas, and our own favorite flavor memories.  Fortunately for everyone, the seasonal theme always seems to yield a beautifully cohesive variety of flavors.  What grows together goes together, you know?

&nbsp;

My mind is constantly blown by the creative and unexpected favorite pairings that our scoopers and customers come up with.  We think we know what y’all will like, but we just don’t.  Cilantro Lime with Coconut, Peanut Butter &amp; Chocolate Swirl?  I never would have anticipated this one, but our South Lamar scoopers (Tamara in particular) vow that together they’re life-changing.  Goat Cheese, Thyme &amp; Honey with Roasted Beets &amp; Fresh Mint is another year-round favorite because, as Claudia at South Lamar told me, goat cheese tastes like happiness and beets look like happiness.  How could you go wrong with that?

&nbsp;

We’re just a couple of weeks away from rotating our seasonal flavors (again!), but there’s still plenty of time to try these favorite pairings of the season:

