Each day I get to come to work and share what I love with some truly amazing individuals.  We inspire each other, we laugh, we encourage one another, we work hard and we make some damn good ice cream.  To say that I am truly overwhelmed by their level of creativity, compassion and dedication is an understatement.

&nbsp;

So, it dawned on me that none of y'all get to have the pleasure of knowing these kind, genuine folks.  I just don't feel that is fair.  To remedy this, we're going to profile some of our staff over the next year.  I've compiled a list of questions for each person to complete that will allow you to get to know them as I do.

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: right;">-  Anthony Sobotik,  co-owner &amp; chef</p>
&nbsp;

First up is our lovely office manager.  Everyone,  meet Juliet!

&nbsp;

<strong>Full name: </strong>Juliet Anelie Dill

&nbsp;

<strong>Date of Birth</strong>:  December 8th, 1977

&nbsp;

<strong>Natural Hair Color</strong>:  Red!!

&nbsp;

<strong>Favorite color(s)</strong>:  Deep blue, Magenta, Purple, and Emerald Green

&nbsp;

<strong>What I love most about living in Austin</strong>:  Being a Mama of a 3.5 year old little boy, my husband and I love all the things Austin has to offer families.  There aren't many towns where you can go out and meet your friends, have a drink while the kids play, and listen to some amazing live music.  Austin also has so much art and community based events centered around nature, farming, and creativity.  In its heart though, Austin is a little hippie town with great style and a funky vibe that brings together an eclectic mix of people.  Last but certainly not least -- TacoDeli breakfast tacos.  When we moved to Boulder a few years ago, breakfast tacos were nowhere to be found and we were in a breakfast fog for the four year we lived there.

&nbsp;

<strong>Favorite musician (doesn't have to be Madonna, but it couldn't hurt)</strong>:  Well besides Madonna, of course... There's no way I can pick only one; my favorites are G. Love, John Butler, Art Tatum, Amos Lee, The Black Keys, Blind Melon, Van Morrisson, Eddie Bedder, Imogen Heap, and you know a lil' Beyonce never hurts.

&nbsp;

<strong>Cat or dog person: </strong>Dog!! (or hedgehog)

&nbsp;

<strong>Favorite 'life saying' or quote or 'words to live by': </strong>If you want to know what "should have" happened, look at what "did" happen.

&nbsp;

<strong>What I do at Lick</strong>:  I'm the office manager and right hand gal for the amazing owners, Anthony and Chad.  I handle wholesale, event coordination, bookkeeping, charitable domations, and anything else they throw my way.

&nbsp;

<strong>Why I love my job</strong>:  I love how Lick participates in the community and gives so much back to the people of Austin.  I love supporting local farms and artisans and on the flipside the magic that brings to our business.  I love how Lick truly is an honest company in every facet of the business.  I am grateful to work with an amazing group of individuals that light up my days.  Each and every member of our team has such a big heart and huge personality.  "The boys," as I collectively call Anthony and Chad, are two of the best bosses I could ask for.  They are incredibly approachable, always open to growth, and move through challenges with grace and humor.  It feels like we are all in this together and it's always a team effort.  But I will say that my most favorite thing about my job is how much I laugh.  Seriously.  My days are full of laughter and it makes my world a lighter place.

&nbsp;

<strong>Time with Lick</strong>:  9 months

&nbsp;

<strong>Why I love ice cream</strong>:  Ice cream makes everyone happy!

&nbsp;

<strong>Favorite flavor</strong>:  Blushing Blueberry.... Oh how I can't wait for its return.  A couple weeks ago, our kitchen manager, Diana, found some forgotten pints of it in the freezer and I thought I'd died and gone to heaven with a spoon.  Two scoops!

